{
  "text": "Other than CCK2R sensitization through SALPC photodynamic action, we also examined photodynamic CCK2R modulation with the genetically encoded protein photosensitizer miniSOG. miniSOG (106 residues) with a noncovalently bound fluorophore flavin mononucleotide (FMN) is a protein photosensitizer with sufficient 1 O 2 quantum yield (≥0.03) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Other than generating 1 O 2 , miniSOG, upon excitation with blue light (448 nm), also emits green (500 nm) fluorescence [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and therefore can be used as a fluorescent tag for protein subcellular localization and protein-protein interactions [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "3387842",
